      <h3>Roles and Development</h3>
      <p>
        This game was a <strong>solo project,</strong> made during the 29th
        Ludum Dare Game Jam. The theme for the Jam was
        <q>Beneath the Surface.</q> The game was developed for both Linux and
        Windows.
      </p>
      <p>
        Hymn of the Moles was written in <strong>C++</strong> with
        <strong>OpenGL, SDL2, and FMOD.</strong> Most of the library code was
        written ahead of the Game Jam. I made this game while in high school,
        before I had any exposure to Linear Algebra, and in hindsight it would
        have been much easier to create using matrices to perform linear
        transformations.
        <span title="At least I didn&rsquo;t try this with a 3D game"
          >Instead, much of the scaling/rotation transformations were manually
          coded!</span
        >
      </p>
      <p>The game uses music and characters by The Residents.</p>
